(17, 1, '2015-10-27 15:42:52', '2015-10-27 15:42:52', '[caption id="attachment_42" align="aligncenter" width="549"]<img class="size-full wp-image-42" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/unnamed-1.jpg" alt="From Left: Audrey Roeder, Martha Gros, Eddy Henry, Lona Shipp, and Leah Manlove Howard" width="549" height="350" /> From Left: Audrey Roeder, Martha Gros, Eddy Henry, Lona Shipp, and Leah Manlove Howard[/caption]\r\n<table width="100%">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2><strong>John Manlove Marketing &amp; Communications dominates developer marketing categories at 2015 GHBA''s Prism Awards.</strong></h2>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table width="100%">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Houston advertising agency <strong>John Manlove Marketing &amp; Communications (JMMC)</strong>exited the <strong>2015 Prism Awards</strong> stage with 13 total awards including the prestigious Promotional Grand Award for Bridgeland.Awards included work for <strong>Howard Hughes Corporation, The Woodlands, Bridgeland and The Signorelli Company</strong>.\r\n\r\n"Its been an exciting year for JMMC. We''ve been pleased with the success of our efforts, but it''s even more rewarding to be recognized by the top professionals in the real estate industry," said JMMC Chief Creative Officer, Eddy Henry.\r\n\r\nThe list of awards in the developer category included:\r\n\r\n<strong>Grand Award for Promotion - Bridgeland</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Marketing Campaign of the Year - Bridgeland Walk-a-bout Spring Home Tour</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Billboard of the Year - The Signorelli Company</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Billboard of the Year Finalist - Bridgeland</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Interactive Point of Sale Experience - Bridgeland</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Event of the Year - Bridgeland Hidden Creek Grand Opening</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Event of the Year Finalist - The Woodlands 40th Anniversary</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Event of the Year Finalist - Bridgeland Howl-o-ween Fest</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Print Ad of the Year - Bridgeland</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Sales Brochure of the Year - Bridgeland Hidden Creek</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=00195aggvmmusN25dttxFSa6xIsrji_8lDXFapvKkiaGPCm_HaH8O8bUZxagqX0cxPBQN-TxP3s1z9OGoBWA6nTj9eQcUe-blOqoyiCVu7u7fLCwfiNZCLOL92o9Q1u9YT-68W8vKgDKgrwLd9-X3DLmzeC8E-4FOEFsI0F4tEJTsyIh89MLlYEGmH7uN8oSqDpF4AEWwth6p4=&amp;c=21Efawb5HGXYnhMmA8vUoAJtft5-p_VScBvUwOYVxajz-7vrfiVAFw==&amp;ch=5maVuLLnH8vpQQeVnJCkWrFbosU-XF-Eyj6V2Ry_CMaOU0r5XcWYMg==">Television/Video Promotion of the Year</a> - Bridgeland</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=00195aggvmmusN25dttxFSa6xIsrji_8lDXFapvKkiaGPCm_HaH8O8bUZxagqX0cxPBhZOZOm0O5Gzk6MTzZ8GHUmxi6KoT9lkdQY_1DnDyIIBvwThiGkHUExjiJ95LfWME7QVThMLT1zeCc2CtiACkOopKBGyWFA43b2NNkm-TgSsCU8qaMnAkKBh2xPyEL8rirdwY1YMFCTg=&amp;c=21Efawb5HGXYnhMmA8vUoAJtft5-p_VScBvUwOYVxajz-7vrfiVAFw==&amp;ch=5maVuLLnH8vpQQeVnJCkWrFbosU-XF-Eyj6V2Ry_CMaOU0r5XcWYMg==">Television/Video Promotion of the Year Finalist</a> - The Signorelli Company</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?f=00195aggvmmusN25dttxFSa6xIsrji_8lDXFapvKkiaGPCm_HaH8O8bUZxagqX0cxPBoHBnwp_0dWDC-hC8K0-j_EOqvaHswoW76su7nNSCUMJtj7HxqlPqxprFYapKy2L7Q133zmp6gFNkb3AAhMiOFhmrtECqMplJfJU6U0ICEHk=&amp;c=21Efawb5HGXYnhMmA8vUoAJtft5-p_VScBvUwOYVxajz-7vrfiVAFw==&amp;ch=5maVuLLnH8vpQQeVnJCkWrFbosU-XF-Eyj6V2Ry_CMaOU0r5XcWYMg==">Website of the Year</a> - Bridgeland</strong>\r\n\r\nLong time JMMC client The Woodlands also won Master Planned Community of the year.\r\n\r\n"The awards are a stunning display of our team''s dedication to great creative. It''s fabulous to win so many prestigious awards in such a competitive market like Houston." - noted Leah Manlove Howard, JMMC Executive Vice President.\r\n\r\nIn addition to the long list of awards, JMMC also chose the annual show as the launch point of an innovative process that will result in the selection of three new partner/client