(642, 1, '2015-12-02 19:21:40', '2015-12-02 19:21:40', '[su_row class="featured-case"]\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/2"]\r\n<h1>Energy</h1>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p class="p1"><span class="s1">Our headquarters are in Houston, Texas. Do we really need to say more? Manlove''s roots are in energy, and we understand the industry from the well up. Whether it’s the latest seismic activity testing or a new refinery process we have the experience and knowledge to communicate effectively to the energy audience you strive to reach. While traditional energy related products and services have been an agency staple, we have also had the opportunity to work with new and alternative sources of energy such as wind. Check out the case study on WETT and see just one example of the remarkable results we’ve been able to achieve for our energy related clients.</span></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n[/su_column]\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/2"]<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-644" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/energy_main.jpg" alt="energy_main" width="600" height="600" /> [/su_column]\r\n\r\n[/su_row]\r\n\r\n[su_row class="secondary"]\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/2" class="float-img"]<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-645" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/energy_float.jpg" alt="energy_float" width="600" height="824" />[/su_column]\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/2"]\r\n<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-646" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/cameron_logo.jpg" alt="cameron_logo" width="300" height="65" /></h2>\r\nFor 15 years John Manlove Marketing and Communications (JMMC) helped Cameron communicate its story and its growth through annual reports. Over this period, Cameron became one of the largest and most profitable suppliers in the energy market, and JMMC worked closely with Investor Relations to achieve their communication goals.\r\n\r\nOne notable milestone of this long-standing relationship was in 2007. Cameron had just had another record year, thanks in part to their rapidly growing branches and subsidiaries in foreign countries. The theme developed for the an-nual report was “Everywhere… and right here”. To truly establish the company’s worldwide presence JMMC planned and implemented a world photography tour, with photo shoots in eight locations around the globe including China, Brazil, Singapore, the United States and several countries in Europe. It took nearly two months to complete, but the result was an incredible library of photography from four continents.\r\n\r\nJMMC also designed and produced a complimentary hardcover coffee table book documenting Cameron’s worldwide presence. Cameron uses the book “Discover our World” as a special gift for partners, investors and employees.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.c-a-m.com" target="_blank">www.c-a-m.com</a>\r\n\r\n[/su_column]\r\n\r\n[/su_row]\r\n\r\n[su_row class="cs-content"]\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/2" class="content"]\r\n<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-650" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/wett_logo.jpg" alt="wett_logo" width="300" height="92" /></h2>\r\nWETT is a start-up company with two foreign parent companies, one in Canada and the other in Spain. With no presence in Texas the company relied on JMMC to help build the branding strategy from the ground up. Working on a very short schedule that revolved around an immovable Texas Legislature timeline JMMC created a variety of materials to create influence and build awareness of the company and their services.\r\n\r\nThe website was the central focus of the marketing strategy with printed collateral, signage, trade show graphics and specialty items all designed to drive traffic to the site. A content and project management system was also set in place on the website so each corporate entity could make changes seamlessly across various time zones.\r\n\r\nThe result was the creation of a complete and unified corporate identity within a few short months and the award of a $500,000,000 contract to help build Texas’ Wind Energy infrastructure.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.windenergyoftexas.com" target="_blank">www.windenergyoftexas.com</a>\r\n\r\n[/su_column]\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/2"]<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-651" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/wett_picture.jpg" alt="wett_picture" width="600" height="601" />[/su_column]\r\n\r\n[/su_row]\r\n\r\n[su_row class="cs-content"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/2"]<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-652" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/wm_picture.jpg" alt="wm_picture" width="600" height="600" />[/su_column]\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/2" class="content"]\r\n<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-653" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/wm_logo.jpg" alt="wm_logo" width="300" height="109" /></h2>\r\nJohn Manlove Marketing &amp; Communications (JMMC) was hired by John Drury CEO of USA Waste Company to rebrand his company. Upon analysis of the current brand identity of USA Waste and the industry at large, it was noted that all the major waste companies were marketing themselves the same way. All marketing materials were very institutional and all were competing for the number of landfills, trucks and capacities they owned. JMMC rebranded USA Waste as an environmentally friendly company all services were positioned from the customer perspective and benefit. The new brand identity was a huge success and redefined the entire waste industry and the way they marketed themselves. USA Waste bought Waste Management Company, the largest Waste Management company in the nation which had $13 billion a year annual revenue at the time. The new Brand Identity that JMMC created for USA Waste was carried over to the newly merged company and to this day waste companies continue to follow the JMMC brand approach.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.wm.com" target="_blank">www.wm.com</a>\r\n\r\n[/su_column]\r\n\r\n[/su_row]\r\n\r\n[su_row class="featured-image"]\r\n\r\n[su_column size="1/1"]\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-657" src="http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/img_energy_featured.jpg" alt="img_energy_featured" width="1200" height="602" />\r\n\r\n[/su_column]\r\n\r\n[/su_row]', 'Energy', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'energy', '', '', '2015-12-04 17:31:54', '2015-12-04 17:31:54', '', 183, 'http://localhost:8888/JMMC_Corp-Site/?page_id=642', 0, 'page', '', 0),
